      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(subagents): preserve requester wake on visible delivery failure",
        "body": "## Summary\n- split requester wake success from visible message-tool delivery status for subagent completions\n- preserve requester/parent wake when required group/channel visible delivery fails to produce message-tool evidence\n- persist visible delivery failure details and mark linked detached task delivery as failed instead of delivered\n\n## Why\nFor group/channel subagent completions, visible replies must still go through the message tool. When that visible delivery fails, the requester/parent wake should remain visible to orchestration instead of becoming a passive `pendingFinalDelivery` dead letter. The visible failure also must not be reported as successful task delivery.\n\nThis keeps the safety policy intact while preserving parent continuation and making task delivery accounting honest.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n**Behavior addressed:** subagent completion delivery where requester/parent handoff runs but the required group/channel visible reply does not produce message-tool evidence.\n\n**Current PR head tested:** `b84c800f6bad93d2d1213f2028a74b4cb1dd6596`\n\n**Real environment tested:** local OpenClaw source checkout on this PR branch, using the patched subagent registry lifecycle with a redacted current-head proof harness. The harness used an active requester session shape, a group/channel route represented as `message_tool_only`, and injected the required-message-tool no-evidence delivery result at the lifecycle boundary so the patched persistence/task-delivery behavior could be observed without posting to a real workspace.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n```bash\nnode --import tsx '<redacted-temp-proof-script>'\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:** terminal output from the current-head local OpenClaw lifecycle proof harness:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"head\": \"b84c800f6bad93d2d1213f2028a74b4cb1dd6596\",\n  \"scenario\": {\n    \"requester\": \"active parent session\",\n    \"visibleRoute\": \"group/channel completion configured as message_tool_only\",\n    \"inducedVisibleFailure\": \"announce agent returned no message-tool delivery evidence\",\n    \"expectedOutcome\": \"requester wake is credited as delivered while visible delivery failure metadata and linked task delivery failure are recorded\"\n  },\n  \"deliveryResult\": {\n    \"delivered\": true,\n    \"path\": \"direct\",\n    \"requesterWakeStatus\": \"delivered\",\n    \"visibleDeliveryRequired\": true,\n    \"visibleDeliveryStatus\": \"failed\",\n    \"visibleDeliveryError\": \"completion agent did not deliver through the message tool\",\n    \"error\": \"completion agent did not deliver through the message tool\"\n  },\n  \"finalRunRecordDelivery\": {\n    \"status\": \"failed\",\n    \"requesterWakeDeliveredAt\": 1779694617674,\n    \"visibleRequired\": true,\n    \"visibleStatus\": \"failed\",\n    \"visibleError\": \"completion agent did not deliver through the message tool\",\n    \"deliveredAt\": 1779694617674,\n    \"lastError\": \"completion agent did not deliver through the message tool\",\n    \"announcedAt\": 1779694617674\n  },\n  \"detachedTaskDeliveryStatusUpdates\": [\n    {\n      \"runId\": \"pr-85308-proof-run\",\n      \"runtime\": \"subagent\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:worker:subagent:pr-85308-proof-child\",\n      \"deliveryStatus\": \"failed\",\n      \"error\": \"completion agent did not deliver through the message tool\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"keyAssertions\": {\n    \"requesterWakeDeliveredAt\": true,\n    \"deliveryStatusFailed\": true,\n    \"visibleCompletionDeliveryRequired\": true,\n    \"visibleCompletionDeliveryStatus\": \"failed\",\n    \"visibleCompletionDeliveryError\": \"completion agent did not deliver through the message tool\",\n    \"completionAnnouncedAt\": true,\n    \"completionDeliveredAt\": true,\n    \"pendingFinalDeliveryCleared\": true,\n    \"cleanupCompleted\": true,\n    \"linkedTaskDeliveryStatusFailed\": true,\n    \"noUnexpectedResume\": true,\n    \"noFallbackSendMessage\": true\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** requester wake was recorded as delivered; `entry.delivery.status` became `failed`; visible delivery was marked required and failed; the pending delivery payload was cleared; cleanup completed; no fallback `sendMessage` path ran; and the linked detached task delivery status was set to `failed` with the visible-delivery error.\n\n**What was not tested:** this proof did not send a live Slack/Discord message to an external channel. It intentionally exercises the required-message-tool no-evidence failure path in a redacted local current-head harness so the PR can show requester wake, persisted visible failure metadata, and failed linked task-delivery status without posting to a real workspace.\n\n## Tests\n- `./node_modules/.bin/vitest run src/agents/subagent-announce-delivery.test.ts src/agents/subagent-registry-lifecycle.test.ts` — 176 passed\n- focused Vitest cases for requester wake / visible delivery failure / task delivery status — 12 passed\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.core.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core.tsbuildinfo`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core-test.tsbuildinfo`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/agents/subagent-announce-dispatch.ts src/agents/subagent-announce-delivery.ts src/agents/subagent-registry-lifecycle.ts src/agents/subagent-registry.types.ts src/agents/subagent-announce-delivery.test.ts src/agents/subagent-registry-lifecycle.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Notes\n- This PR intentionally treats requester wake success as terminal for this failure mode while reporting required visible delivery as failed.\n- If maintainers want required visible output to keep retrying until message-tool evidence exists or retry limits expire, this should shift to a retry-preserving design instead.\n",
        "branch": "fix/subagent-visible-delivery-parent-wake",
